SIMPLE: inviolated
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inviolated
<hw>In*vi"o*la`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>inviolatus</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Violate</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not violated; uninjured; unhurt; unbroken.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His fortune of arms was still <qex>inviolate</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not corrupted, defiled, or profaned; chaste;
pure.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Inviolate</xex> truth.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Denham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There chaste Alceste lives <qex>inviolate</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inviolately</ent>⟦br⟧
